<p align="center"><font color="#0E024D" face="Arial"><strong>PLAYER SUBMITTED STRATEGY</strong></font></p>
<div align="center"><center>

  <div align="center"><center><table border="0" width="90%">
    <tr>
      <td>
      <center><font face="Arial"><strong><b><font color="#800000">HOW TO TEACH THOSE KILL STEALING WIZARDS A LESSON</b></font> - <small>Ronnin, Tunare</small></strong></font><font face="Arial"></center>
<div align="center"><center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="80%">
  <tr>
    <td>
    <small><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><P>
    This works great when you are in a group and in a free for all zone (like highhold pass orc zone). This is what commonly happens, you are in a group with 6 people, the spawn comes and you tanks jump to battle, as the 3 to 4 mobs start pounding on your tanks, that wizard, or pair of wizards in the corner target the highst lvl mob and unleash a fury of unholy fire power on it, killing it dead and stealing your group's hard earned experiance, as the enchanter you have the means to fight back, and here is how to do it, target the wizard, as the spawn comes and the battle ensue's hit your hot key for assist, you will automaticly target whatever the wizard has targeted, charm that mob, and immediatly tell it to attack another mob next to it. it will look like it is still attacking the tanks, and the wizard's will continue to use up all there mana trying to send that mob to an early grave, by this time your tanks have finished killing all the other mob's and the wizards are all dryed up. then take your charmed mob to a safe area and make sure your fighters are around you and ready, then cast invis on yourself to break the charm, the mob will attack you, but will soon turn its attack on the fighters pummiling it to death. This tecnique has worked wonders for me in all kill stealing situations, one important point is that you maintain good communications with your group via group talk and tell them exactly what mob you have charmed and so on. Try it youll like it.
    </small></font></p>
    <p><small><font face="Arial">&nbsp;</font></small></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td><center><hr size="1" color="#C0C0C0"><p align="center"><small><strong><font face="Arial">
